		<credit project="CfPBoK@https://slebok.github.io/cfpbok/"/>
		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2017"></a><br><code>sle2017/paper08</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2017</a> paper:</span><br><i>A symbol-based extension of parsing expression grammars and context- sensitive packrat parsing</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/KimioKuramitsu.html">Kimio Kuramitsu</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3136014.3136025">10.1145/3136014.3136025</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4d.html"><span class="tagM">T4D: Interpretation</span></a><ul><li> The paper extends PEG-based parsing with context-sensitive capabilities, i.e., runtime parsing/recognition techniques.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> PEGs are treated as a grammar formalism, and the work extends that meta-language with symbol-based mechanisms.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> It targets modular recognition of patterns found in real languages, including composition-like idioms (e.g., typedef-style contexts).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5f.html"><span class="tagL">T5F: Performance</span></a><ul><li> Context-sensitive packrat parsing raises efficiency concerns that the paper addresses as part of practicality.
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
